 |KanjiTitle=<U+6771><U+4EAC>RPG
 |EnglishTitle=Tokyo RPG
 |OriginalAirDate=[[August 9]] [[2007]]
 |ShortSummary=Ren and his friends encounter one of those "magicians" during one of their outings and are attacked by a fire-using one. Ren uses his powers to defeat the "magician," who reveals information on the whereabouts of the "game" known as Pandemonium. Ren decided to check the place suspected to be the headquarters with this information, discovering that it is in another dimension. As he prepares to leave, he is suddenly teleported inside thhe building. Meanwhile, Tachibana calls for Kazuma to regroup at the Kannagi's place to discuss further plans.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber=19
 |JapaneseTitle=Pandemoniumu
 |KanjiTitle=<U+30D1><U+30F3><U+30C7><U+30E2><U+30CB><U+30A6><U+30E0>
 |EnglishTitle=Pandemonium
 |OriginalAirDate=[[August 16]] [[2007]]
 |ShortSummary=Kirika briefs everyone about the recent events and its connection to the game Pandemonium which caused the players to "download" youma through the net unknowingly. After they learn that Ren has been kidnapped, Kazuma, Ayano, and Tachibana enter Pandemonium. Ayano fights [[Kaze no Stigma#Enemies|Lapis]], who has the appearance of Tsui-Ling. Meanwhile, Kazuma finds Ren, and identifies the man behind Pandemonium as [[Kaze no Stigma#Enemies|Burnheart Rhodes]], a former enemy he defeated in the past.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber=20
 |JapaneseTitle=Suishoku no Zan Kage
 |KanjiTitle=<U+7FE0><U+8272><U+306E><U+6B8B><U+5F71>
 |EnglishTitle=Jade Afterimage
 |OriginalAirDate=[[August 23]] [[2007]]
 |ShortSummary=Kazuma questions Burnheart about Lapis and denies that the girl is Tsui-Ling, whom Burnheart sacrificed to a demon. Burnheart in turn, replies that the girl Lapis was that of what remained of Tsui-Ling whom Kazuma failed to protect due to his lack of power. As Kazuma attempts to attack Burnheart, Lapis deflects the blow and shows her power as a "Swordsmaster" by slicing the building they were in in half. Kazuma saves Ren, Ayano, and Kirika but disappears soon after. Back at the Kannagi home, Kirika informs them that a new Pandemonium has appeared and has granted "class changes" to some of its players. Meanwhile, Kazuma, brooding over the happiness of his past with Tsui-Ling, resolves to kill Burnheart and Lapis.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber=21
 |JapaneseTitle=Ky<U+014D>ran no Kazejutsushi
 |KanjiTitle=<U+72C2><U+4E71><U+306E><U+98A8><U+8853><U+5E2B>
 |EnglishTitle=The Mad Wind Mage
 |OriginalAirDate=[[August 30]] [[2007]]
 |ShortSummary=Since the new Pandemonium appeared, battles held every night which pitched "magicians" together in a battle and the winner gains experience points. Kazuma appears at these battles, brutally attacking the combatants and asking them on the location of Pandemonium. He goes so far as to assault Katherine and allow Nanase to be kidnapped. Afterwards, Tachibana informs Ayano that Kazuma has regressed to his former cold-hearted persona, and only Ayano can bring him back.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber=22
 |JapaneseTitle=Ketsui to Shunjun to
 |KanjiTitle=<U+6C7A><U+610F><U+3068><U+9021><U+5DE1><U+3068>
 |EnglishTitle=Determination and Hesitation
 |OriginalAirDate=[[September 6]] [[2007]]
 |ShortSummary=Ren, Suzuhara and Serizawa witness Kazuma battle with one of the magicians. Later, Yukari goes to a meeting of seeds, where Utsumi tells them that Pandemonium will appear in the park at midnight and that they may achieve great power if they went there. At Pandemonium, Utsumi tells Burnheart that he wants to take over and that he will kill Burnheart. However, Burnheart responds by saying that he was the one who gave Utsumi power in the first place.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber=23
 |JapaneseTitle=Beni En
 |KanjiTitle=<U+7D05><U+708E>
 |EnglishTitle=The Crimson Flame
 |OriginalAirDate=[[September 13]] [[2007]]
 |ShortSummary=At the hospital Katherine speaks with Ayano, and increases her resolve to save Kazuma. Ayano and Ren convince Jugo and Genma to let them try to bring Kazuma back after Genma states that he will kill Kazuma and Burnheart. When Pandemonium appears, Ayano and Ren encounter Kazuma. Kazuma tells Ayano and Ren that he is not trying to destroy Pandemonium because of Tsui-Ling but simply because he wants to kill Burnheart. Ayano summons the Enraiha and attacks Kazuma. She thinks about what she learned from Kazuma and unknowingly uses the Crimson Flame. She manages to convince Kazuma to stop killing innocent people. Kazuma realizes that he has someone new in his life that has great importance, and the three set out to destroy Pandemonium.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber=24
 |JapaneseTitle=Kaze no mamorishi mono
 |KanjiTitle=<U+98A8><U+306E><U+8B77><U+308A><U+3057><U+3082><U+306E>
 |EnglishTitle=Protectors of the Wind
 |OriginalAirDate=[[September 20]] [[2007]]
 |ShortSummary=Kazuma, Ayano and Ren encounter Lapis, Nanase and Yukari. Lapis begins the summoning ritual of Belial, the King of Demons. Lapis reveals she is doing all of this, to become "human." Kazuma and Ayano attack Lapis, who retreats as Belial's summoning proceeds. By combining their powers, Kazuma, Ayano, and Ren manage to repel Belial. Afterwards, Burnheart and Lapis approach them, with Gemna's presence convincing Burnheart not to kill them. Before they leave, Kazuma asks what were those final thoughts of Tsui-Ling from Lapis, who reveals that Tsui-Ling wanted to kill Kazuma before she died. Back at the Kannagi residence, Kazuma reveals he has accepted his past and will concentrate on the future, which incenses Ayano, who claims that she does not always need to be protected, and that Kazuma should rely on her. Kazuma agrees, but gives Ayano a spank in the process, resulting in Ayano angrily chasing him around the courtyard as the members of the Kannagi family, Ren's and Ayano's friends, and Tachibana look on amused.
}}
